  "description": "Porch and replacement window to converted garage to the front elevation, block up side door and new bi-fold doors on rear elevation",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "The development to which this permission relates must be commenced not later than three years from the date of this permission.",
    "Reason:-",
    "To comply with the requirements of Section 91 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended by Section 51 of the Planning and Compulsory Purchase Act 2004).",
    "Prior to any above ground works, a written specification of external walls and roof materials to be used in the construction of the proposed development, including the details of the materials and finishes to the porch, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority and thereafter the development shall be constructed with the approved materials.",
    "Reason:-",
    "Insufficient information has been supplied with the application to judge the appropriateness of the materials to be used.  Submission of a written specification prior to any above ground works will ensure that the appearance of the proposed development will harmonise with the character of the surrounding area and the Havering-atte-Bower Conservation Area and comply with Policies DC61 and DC68 of",
    "The development hereby permitted shall not be carried out otherwise than in complete accordance with the approved plans (as set out on page one of this decision notice).",
    "Reason:-",
    "For the avoidance of doubt and to ensure that the development is carried out as approved.",
    "Statement Required by Article 35 (2) of the Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015: In accordance with paragraph 38 of the National Planning Policy Framework 2018, improvements required to make the proposal acceptable were negotiated with Hedgehog Development via email on 15th January 2021. The revisions involved removing the roof light from the front roof slope and replacing the double door to the porch with a single timber door. The amendments were subsequently submitted on 15th January 2021."
